1003.definition: [Βοόζ] of Hebrew origin ({{H1162}}); Booz, (i.e. Boaz), an Israelite

1005.definition: [βοῤῥᾶς] of uncertain derivation; the north (properly, wind)

1006.definition: [βόσκω] a prolonged form of a primary verb (compare {{G977}}, {{G1016}}); to pasture; by extension to, fodder; reflexively, to graze

1007.definition: [Βοσόρ] of Hebrew origin ({{H1160}}); Bosor (i.e. Beor), a Moabite

1009.definition: [βότρυς] of uncertain derivation; a bunch (of grapes)

1010.definition: [βουλευτής] from {{G1011}}; an adviser, i.e. (specially) a councillor or member of the Jewish Sanhedrin

1011.definition: [βουλεύω] from {{G1012}}; to advise, i.e. (reflexively) deliberate, or (by implication) resolve

1012.definition: [βουλή] from {{G1014}}; volition, i.e. (objectively) advice, or (by implication) purpose

1014.definition: [βούλομαι] middle voice of a primary verb; to "will," i.e. (reflexively) be willing Compare {{G2309}}.

1015.definition: [βουνός] probably of foreign origin; a hillock

1016.definition: [βοῦς] probably from the base of {{G1006}}; an ox (as grazing), i.e. an animal of that species ("beef")

1017.definition: [βραβεῖον] from βραβεύς (an umpire of uncertain derivation); an award (of arbitration), i.e. (specially) a prize in the public games

1018.definition: [βραβεύω] from the same as {{G1017}}; to arbitrate, i.e. (genitive case) to govern (figuratively, prevail)

1020.definition: [βραδυπλοέω] from {{G1021}} and a prolonged form of {{G4126}}; to sail slowly

1021.definition: [βραδύς] of uncertain affinity; slow; figuratively, dull

1023.definition: [βραχίων] properly, comparative of {{G1024}}, but apparently in the sense of βράσσω (to wield); the arm, i.e. (figuratively) strength

1024.definition: [βραχύς] of uncertain affinity; short (of time, place, quantity, or number)

1025.definition: [βρέφος] of uncertain affinity; an infant (properly, unborn) literally or figuratively

1026.definition: [βρέχω] a primary verb; to moisten (especially by a shower)

1031.definition: [βρύχω] a primary verb; to grate the teeth (in pain or rage)

1032.definition: [βρύω] a primary verb; to swell out, i.e. (by implication) to gush

1033.definition: [βρῶμα] from the base of {{G977}}; food (literally or figuratively), especially (ceremonially) articles allowed or forbidden by the Jewish law

1035.definition: [βρῶσις] from the base of {{G977}}; (abstractly) eating (literally or figuratively); by extension (concretely) food (literally or figuratively)

1036.definition: [βυθίζω] from {{G1037}}; to sink; by implication, to drown

1037.definition: [βυθός] a variation of {{G899}}; depth, i.e. (by implication) the sea

1039.definition: [βύσσινος] from {{G1040}}; made of linen (neuter a linen cloth)

1041.definition: [βωμός] from the base of {{G939}}; properly, a stand, i.e. (specially) an altar

1042.definition: [γαββαθά] of Chaldee origin (compare {{H1355}}); the knoll; gabbatha, a vernacular term for the Roman tribunal in Jerusalem

1043.definition: [Γαβριήλ] of Hebrew origin ({{H1403}}); Gabriel, an archangel

1045.definition: [Γάδ] of Hebrew origin ({{H1410}}); Gad, a tribe of Israelites

1046.definition: [Γαδαρηνός] from Γαδαρά (a town east of the Jordan); a Gadarene or inhabitant of Gadara

1048.definition: [Γάζα] of Hebrew origin ({{H5804}}); Gazah (i.e. Azzah), a place in Palestine

1049.definition: [γαζοφυλάκιον] from {{G1047}} and {{G5438}}; a treasure-house, i.e. a court in the temple for the collection-boxes

1050.definition: [Γάϊος] of Latin origin; Gaius (i.e. Caius), a Christian

1052.definition: [Γαλάτης] from {{G1053}}; a Galatian or inhabitant of Galatia

1053.definition: [Γαλατία] of foreign origin; Galatia, a region of Asia

1054.definition: [Γαλατικός] from {{G1053}}; Galatic or relating to Galatia

1056.definition: [Γαλιλαία] of Hebrew origin ({{H1551}}); Galilæa (i.e. the heathen circle), a region of Palestine

1057.definition: [Γαλιλαῖος] from {{G1056}}; Galilean or belonging to Galilea

1058.definition: [Γαλλίων] of Latin origin; Gallion (i.e. Gallio), a Roman officer

1059.definition: [Γαμαλιήλ] of Hebrew origin ({{H1583}}); Gamaliel (i.e. Gamliel), an Israelite

1061.definition: [γαμίσκω] from {{G1062}}; to espouse (a daughter to a husband)

1063.definition: [γάρ] a primary particle; properly, assigning a reason (used in argument, explanation or intensification; often with other particles)

1064.definition: [γαστήρ] of uncertain derivation; the stomach; by analogy, the matrix; figuratively, a gourmand

1065.definition: [γέ] a primary particle of emphasis or qualification (often used with other particles prefixed)

1066.definition: [Γεδεών] of Hebrew origin ({{H1439}}); Gedeon (i.e. Gid(e)on), an Israelite

1067.definition: [γέεννα] of Hebrew origin ({{H1516}} and {{H2011}}); valley of (the son of) Hinnom; ge-henna (or Ge-Hinnom), a valley of Jerusalem, used (figuratively) as a name for the place (or state) of everlasting punishment

1068.definition: [Γεθσημανῆ] of Chaldee origin (compare {{H1660}} and {{H8081}}); oil-press; Gethsemane, a garden near Jerusalem

1069.definition: [γείτων] from {{G1093}}; a neighbour (as adjoining one's ground); by implication, a friend

1070.definition: [γελάω] of uncertain affinity; to laugh (as a sign of joy or satisfaction)

1071.definition: [γέλως] from {{G1070}}; laughter (as a mark of gratification)

1073.definition: [γέμω] a primary verb; to swell out, i.e. be full

1074.definition: [γενεά] from (a presumed derivative of) {{G1085}}; a generation; by implication, an age (the period or the persons)

1075.definition: [γενεαλογέω] from {{G1074}} and {{G3056}}; to reckon by generations, i.e. trace in genealogy

1076.definition: [γενεαλογία] from the same as {{G1075}}; tracing by generations, i.e. "genealogy"

1077.definition: [γενέσια] neuter plural of a derivative of {{G1078}}; birthday ceremonies

1078.definition: [γένεσις] from the same as {{G1074}}; nativity; figuratively, nature

1079.definition: [γενετή] feminine of a presumed derivative of the base of {{G1074}}; birth

1080.definition: [γεννάω] from a variation of {{G1085}}; to procreate (properly, of the father, but by extension of the mother); figuratively, to regenerate

1081.definition: [γέννημα] from {{G1080}}; offspring; by analogy, produce (literally or figuratively)

1082.definition: [Γεννησαρέτ] of Hebrew origin (compare {{H3672}}); Gennesaret (i.e. Kinnereth), a lake and plain in Palestine

1085.definition: [γένος] from {{G1096}}; "kin" (abstract or concrete, literal or figurative, individual or collective)

1086.definition: [Γεργεσηνός] of Hebrew origin ({{H1622}}); a Gergesene (i.e. Girgashite) or one of the aborigines of Palestine

1087.definition: [γερουσία] from {{G1088}}; the eldership, i.e. (collectively) the Jewish Sanhedrin

1089.definition: [γεύομαι] a primary verb; to taste; by implication, to eat; figuratively, to experience (good or ill)

1091.definition: [γεώργιον] neuter of a (presumed) derivative of {{G1092}}; cultivable, i.e. a farm

1092.definition: [γεωργός] from {{G1093}} and the base of {{G2041}}; a land-worker, i.e. farmer

1093.definition: [γῆ] contracted from a primary word; soil; by extension a region, or the solid part or the whole of the terrene globe (including the occupants in each application)

1096.definition: [γίνομαι] a prolongation and middle voice form of a primary verb; to cause to be ("gen"-erate), i.e. (reflexively) to become (come into being), used with great latitude (literal, figurative, intensive, etc.)

1097.definition: [γινώσκω] a prolonged form of a primary verb; to "know" (absolutely) in a great variety of applications and with many implications (as follow, with others not thus clearly expressed)

1098.definition: [γλεῦκος] akin to {{G1099}}; sweet wine, i.e. (properly) must (fresh juice), but used of the more saccharine (and therefore highly inebriating) fermented wine

1099.definition: [γλυκύς] of uncertain affinity; sweet (i.e. not bitter nor salt)

1100.definition: [γλῶσσα] of uncertain affinity; the tongue; by implication, a language (specially, one naturally unacquired)
